{"title_page": "Luxor Records", "text_new": "{{infobox record label\n| name = Luxor Records\n| image = Luxor Records.png\n| image_bg = \n| parent = \n| founded = 2007\n| founder = {{Unbulleted list|Nick Morris|Aaron Bridgewater}}\n| distributor = [[Victory Records|Victory]]\n| genre = [[Metalcore]], [[Deathcore]], [[Nu-metal]]\n| country = [[United States]]\n| location = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]\n| url = \n}}\n\n'''Luxor Records''' is an American record label located in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]].\n\n==Background==\nLuxor Records was co-founded by Aaron Bridgewater (lead vocals) and Nick Morris (lead guitarist), of [[As They Sleep]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hxcmag.com/2016/06/23/label-profile-luxor-records-talk-new-releases-hard-work-artists-first/|title=LABEL PROFILE: Luxor Records Talk New Releases, Hard Work, Artists First|publisher=HXC Magazine|first=Taylor|last=Markarian|date=June 23, 2016|accessdate=October 13, 2016}}</ref> The label was created to release the band's first album, ''[[Blacken the Sun]]'', but later made it professional after signing bands such as It Lies Within and Forsake the Fallen.<ref name=\"Interview 1\">{{cite web|url=http://theperfectscene.net/interview-nick-morris-luxor-records/|title=Interview: Nick Morris of Luxor Records|publisher=Perfect Scene|first=Kevin|last=Bottaro|date=July 2, 2016|accessdate=August 18, 2016}}</ref> Later in 2012, the label signed [[Broken Flesh]], a [[Christian metal]] of the [[extreme metal]] genre.<ref name=\"Metal Resource\"/> More bands were signed throughout 2015\u20132016, such as The Order of Elijah,<ref name=\"Listen Here\"/> [[My Heart to Fear]],<ref name=\"New Noise\"/> [[Toarn]],<ref name=Toarn/> and From Blue to Gray.<ref name=\"Vents\"/>\n\n==Artists==\n\n===Current===\n* [[As They Sleep]]\n* Born With Open Eyes\n* [[Broken Flesh]]<ref name=\"Metal Resource\">{{cite web|url=http://mauce.nl/site/broken-flesh-signs-with-luxor-records-lyric-video-released-for-scorned/|title='Broken Flesh' signs with 'Luxor Records', Lyric Video Released for \"Scorned\"|publisher=The Metal Resource|date=February 17, 2015|accessdate=August 18, 2016}}</ref>\n* Dagon\n* Emuness\n* Forsake the Fallen\n* From Blue to Gray<ref name=\"Vents\">{{cite web|url=https://ventsmagazine.com/2016/06/15/blue-gray-sign-luxor-records-announce-lp-stream-new-track%E2%80%8F/|title=From Blue To Gray Signs Luxor Records, Announce LP, Stream New Track|publisher=Vents Magazine|first=RJ|last=Frometa|date=June 15, 2016|accessdate=August 18, 2016}}</ref>\n* [[A Hill to Die Upon]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indievisionmusic.com/news/hill-die-upon-signs-luxor-records/|title=A Hill to Die Upon Signs to Luxor Records|publisher=Indie Vision Music|first=Mason|last=Beard|date=August 11, 2017|accessdate=August 11, 2017}}</ref>\n* Imminent Sonic Destruction\n* [[It Lies Within]]\n* Kaleido\n* [[Motown Rage]]\n* [[My Heart to Fear]]<ref name=\"New Noise\">{{cite web|url=http://newnoisemagazine.com/heart-fear-luxor-records-stream-track/|title=My Heart To Fear Sign To Luxor Records, Stream New Track|publisher=New Noise Magazine|date=August 4, 2016|accessdate=August 18, 2016}}</ref>\n* The Order of Elijah<ref name=\"Listen Here\">{{cite web|url=http://www.listenherereviews.com/?p=9054|title=Luxor Records signs The Order of Elijah, new album to be released later this year|publisher=Listen Here Reviews|author=Laureng|date=February 13, 2015|accessdate=August 18, 2016}}</ref>\n* Primo Beats\n* Read 'Em and Weep\n* Scream Out Loud\n* {{proper name|Suppy}} Dudes\n* Syphilic\n* [[Toarn]]<ref name=Toarn>{{cite web|url=http://newnoisemagazine.com/toarn-signs-luxor-records/|title=Toarn Signs Luxor Records|publisher=New Noise Magazine|date=June 9, 2016|accessdate=August 18, 2016}}</ref>\n* Upon a Broken Throne\n\n===Former===\n* Cry Excess\n* Duse Breed\n* A Reason to Breathe\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:American record labels]]\n[[Category:Heavy metal record labels]]\n\n\n{{US-record-label-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{infobox record label\n| name = Luxor Records\n| image = Luxor Records.png\n| image_bg = \n| parent = \n| founded = 2007\n| founder = {{Unbulleted list|Nick Morris|Aaron Bridgewater}}\n| distributor = [[Victory Records|Victory]]\n| genre = [[Metalcore]], [[Deathcore]], [[Nu-metal]]\n| country = [[United States]]\n| location = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]\n| url = \n}}\n\n'''Luxor Records''' is an American record label located in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]].\n\n==Background==\nLuxor Records was co-founded by Aaron Bridgewater (lead vocals) and Nick Morris (lead guitarist), of [[As They Sleep]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hxcmag.com/2016/06/23/label-profile-luxor-records-talk-new-releases-hard-work-artists-first/|title=LABEL PROFILE: Luxor Records Talk New Releases, Hard Work, Artists First|publisher=HXC Magazine|first=Taylor|last=Markarian|date=June 23, 2016|accessdate=October 13, 2016}}</ref> The label was created to release the band's first album, ''[[Blacken the Sun]]'', but later made it professional after signing bands such as It Lies Within and Forsake the Fallen.<ref name=\"Interview 1\">{{cite web|url=http://theperfectscene.net/interview-nick-morris-luxor-records/|title=Interview: Nick Morris of Luxor Records|publisher=Perfect Scene|first=Kevin|last=Bottaro|date=July 2, 2016|accessdate=August 18, 2016}}</ref> Later in 2012, the label signed [[Broken Flesh]], a [[Christian metal]] of the [[extreme metal]] genre.<ref name=\"Metal Resource\"/> More bands were signed throughout 2015-2016, such as The Order of Elijah,<ref name=\"Listen Here\"/> [[My Heart to Fear]],<ref name=\"New Noise\"/> [[Toarn]],<ref name=Toarn/> and From Blue to Gray.<ref name=\"Vents\"/>\n\n==Artists==\n\n===Current===\n* [[As They Sleep]]\n* Born With Open Eyes\n* [[Broken Flesh]]<ref name=\"Metal Resource\">{{cite web|url=http://mauce.nl/site/broken-flesh-signs-with-luxor-records-lyric-video-released-for-scorned/|title='Broken Flesh' signs with 'Luxor Records', Ly