nner''' Best Music Director 'S I Tutul' 2007\n* '''Winner''' Best Choreographer: 'Kabirul Islam Ratan' 2007\n* '''Winner''' Best Side Role Actor: 'Abul Hayat' 2007\n* '''Winner''' Best Scriptwriter: '[[Humayun Ahmed]]' 2007\n\n===Meril Prothom Alo Awards===\n\n==Music==\nThe music for ''Daruchini Dwip'' was directed by S I Tutul.\n# \"Dur Dwipobasini\" - [[Samina Chowdhury]] and [[Fahmida Nabi]]\n# \"Monta Jeno Aaj Pakhir Dana\" - [[S I Tutul]] and [[Samina Chowdhury]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|id=2048726|title=Daruchini Dip}}\n* {{rotten-tomatoes|daruchini-dwip|Daruchini Dip}}\n{{Bangladesh National Film Award Best Film}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Daruchini Dip}}\n[[Category:2007 films]]\n[[Category:2000s romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:2000s romantic drama films]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi films]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi romantic drama films]]\n[[Category:Bengali-language films]]\n[[Category:Films based on Bangladeshi novels]]\n[[Category:Films scored by S I Tutul]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Tauquir Ahmed]]\n[[Category:2000s Bengali-language films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2013}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Daruchini Dip\n| image          = Daruchini Dip.jpg\n| image_size     = 200px\n| caption        = DVD Cover\n| director       = [[Tauquir Ahmed]]\n| producer       = Faridur Reza Sagar (Impress Telefilm Ltd.)\n| writer         = [[Humayun Ahmed]]\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Riaz (Actor)|Riaz]]\n* [[Zakia Bari Momo]]\n* [[Mamnun Hasan Emon]]\n* [[Bindu (Actress-Bangladesh)|Bindu]]\n* [[Abul Hayat]]\n* [[Asaduzzaman Noor]]\n* [[Mosharraf Karim]]\n* [[Abdullah al Mamun]]\n* [[Fazlur Rahman Babu]]\n}}\n| music          = S I Tutul\n| cinematography = A R Swapan\n| editing        = Atish Dey Sarkar\n| distributor    = [[Channel i]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2007|08|31|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 126 minutes\n| country        = [[Bangladesh]]\n| language       = [[Bengali language|Bengali]]\n| budget         =\n| gross          =\n}}\n\n'''''Daruchini Dip''''' ({{lang-bn|\u09a6\u09be\u09b0\u09c1\u099a\u09bf\u09a8\u09bf \u09a6\u09cd\u09ac\u09c0\u09aa}}) is a [[Bangladesh]]i [[Bengali-language]] film. It was released on 31 August 2007 throughout Bangladesh. The film is based on the Bangladeshi novelist and film maker [[Humayun Ahmed]]\u2019s popular novel of the same name.<ref>{{cite news | newspaper=The Daily Star | date=18 April 2008 | url=http://www.thedailystar.net/story.php?nid=32549 | title=Reader's Opinion A visit to 'Daruchini Dwip' | first=Farida | last=Reza | accessdate=13 April 2011}}</ref> It was directed: by popular TV actor [[Tauquir Ahmed]].<ref>{{cite news | newspaper=The Daily Star | date=31 August 2007 | url=http://www.thedailystar.net/story.php?nid=1935 | title='Daruchini Dwip' on Channel-i today | accessdate=13 April 2011}}</ref> ''Daruchini Dip'' stars [[Riaz (Actor)|Riaz]], the award-winning [[Zakia Bari Momo]],<ref>{{cite news | newspaper=The Daily Star | date=11 August 2006 | url=http://www.thedailystar.net/2006/08/11/d608111404101.htm | title=Road to 'Daruchini Dwip' Update on 'Lux Channel i Superstar' | accessdate=13 April 2011}}</ref> [[Mamnun Hasan Emon]], Bindu, Abul Hayat, [[Asaduzzaman Noor]], [[Mosharraf Karim]], [[Abdullah al Mamun]], and [[Fazlur Rahman Babu]].\n\nThe film was appreciated by film critics and won the National Film Award of Bangladesh ''Best Film of the Year 2007'' and was nominated in seven categories also won all are.<ref>{{cite news | newspaper=The Daily Star | date=1 September 2008 | url=http://www.thedailystar.net/story.php?nid=52684 | title=National Film Awards for the last fours years announced | accessdate=8 May 2011}}</ref> It also won ''Best Foreign Language Film'' at the 2010 Bali International Film Festival Awards in [[Indonesia]].\n\n==Plot==\nA team of young boys and girls plan to have a big trip across Bangladesh. They all hail from the mega city of [[Dhaka]]. In Bangladesh, being a conservative country, it is not common to the sight of a group consisting of both young, single men and women traveling together. Yet in this story, the girls are seen to try to make it against the stream. Each had a different destination in mind: like [[Sundarban]], [[Cox's Bazar]], [[Saint Martin]] and many more places. Finally they decide to go to '''Daruchini Dip'''. 'Shuvro'([[Riaz (actor)|Riaz]]) has a big problem for his weak eyesight because he may be put out from the program. But finally the full team goes on a train with 'Shuvro'.\n\n==Cast==\n* ''[[Riaz (Actor)|Riaz]]'' - Shuvro / Kana Baba <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dhakatimes24.com/2018/10/26/100992/\u09b8\u09cd\u09a5\u09aa\u09a4\u09bf-\u09b9\u09a4\u09c7-\u099a\u09c7\u09af\u09bc\u09c7-\u09a8\u09be\u09af\u09bc\u0995|script-title=bn:\u09b8\u09cd\u09a5\u09aa\u09a4\u09bf \u09b9\u09a4\u09c7 \u099a\u09c7\u09af\u09bc\u09c7 \u09a8\u09be\u09af\u09bc\u0995|work=Dhaka Times |language=bn|access-date=2019-05-24}}</ref>\n* ''[[Zakia Bari Momo]]'' - Jori<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.prothomalo.com/entertainment/article/1574926/%E0%A6%AF%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%97-%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BF%E0%A7%9F%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%AE|script-title=bn:\u09af\u09c1\u0997 \u09aa\u09c7\u09b0\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09c7 \u09ae\u09ae|work=Prothom Alo|language=bn|access-date=2019-05-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://bonikbarta.net/bangla/fbs/2018-10-03/172440/|script-title=bn:\u0985\u09ad\u09bf\u09a8\u09af\u09bc\u09c7 \u098f\u0995 \u09af\u09c1\u0997 \u09ae\u09ae\u09b0|work=Bonik Barta|language=bn|access-date=2019-05-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190525135028/http://bonikbarta.net/bangla/fbs/2018-10-03/172440/|archive-date=25 May 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* ''[[Mamnun Hasan Emon]]'' - Shonju\n* ''[[Afsana Ara Bindu|Bindu]]'' - Anushka<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.channelionline.com/%e0%a6%89%e0%a6%a8%e0%a6%bf%e0%a6%b6%e0%a7%87%e0%a6%b0-%e0%a6%89%e0%a6%9a%