'Music'' - [[S I Tutul]]\n* ''Editing'' - Atish Day Sarkar\n* ''Sound'' - Anup Mukharjee\n* ''Dress'' - Shahrukh Amin Tingku\n* ''Choreography'' - Kabirul Islam Ratan\n* ''Distributor'' - [[Channel i]]\n\n==Technical details==\n* Format: 35 MM (Color)\n* Real: 13Pans\n* Sub-Title: English\n* Year of the Product: 2006-2007\n* Technical Support: Bangladesh Film Development Corporation (BFDC)\n\n==Awards and achievement==\n\n=== International awards ===\n* '''Winner''' Best Foreign Language Film: Bali International Film Festival Awards 2010 [[Indonesia]].<ref>{{cite news | newspaper=The Daily Star | date=2 December 2010 | url=http://www.thedailystar.net/newDesign/news-details.php?nid=164390 | title=\"Daruchini Dwip\" wins the day Bali International Film Festival / Arts & Entertainment | accessdate=13 April 2011}}</ref>\n\n===National Film Awards===\n''Daruchini Dwip'' won the National Film Awards total seven categories in the year of 2007.\n* '''Winner''' Best Film 'Impress Telefilm Ltd.' 2007\n* '''Winner''' Best Actor: '[[Riaz (Actor)|Riaz]]' 2007\n* '''Winner''' Best Actress: '[[Zakia Bari Momo]]' 2007\n* '''Winner''' Best Music Director 'S I Tutul' 2007\n* '''Winner''' Best Choreographer: 'Kabirul Islam Ratan' 2007\n* '''Winner''' Best Side Role Actor: 'Abul Hayat' 2007\n* '''Winner''' Best Scriptwriter: '[[Humayun Ahmed]]' 2007\n\n===Meril Prothom Alo Awards===\n\n==Music==\nThe music for ''Daruchini Dwip'' was directed by S I Tutul.\n# \"Dur Dwipobasini\" - [[Samina Chowdhury]] and [[Fahmida Nabi]]\n# \"Monta Jeno Aaj Pakhir Dana\" - [[S I Tutul]] and [[Samina Chowdhury]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|id=2048726|title=Daruchini Dip}}\n* {{rotten-tomatoes|daruchini-dwip|Daruchini Dip}}\n{{Bangladesh National Film Award Best Film}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Daruchini Dip}}\n[[Category:2007 films]]\n[[Category:2000s romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:2000s romantic drama films]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi films]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi romantic drama films]]\n[[Category:Bengali-language films]]\n[[Category:Films based on Bangladeshi novels]]\n[[Category:Films scored by S I Tutul]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Tauquir Ahmed]]\n[[Category:2000s Bengali-language films]]\n", "name_user": "Titodutta", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daruchini_Dip"}
